The derivation of the functional Schrodinger 
representation from the precanonical approach  

It is definitely of interest to understand how the functional 
Schrodinger representation of quantum YM theory  
can be related with 
 
precanonical quantization. In what follows 
we will show that the functional differential 
Schrodinger equation can be derived from the 
covariant Schrodinger equation of the precanonical approach. 
The relation of this kind has been studied in the case of scalar 
field theory in. 
 
Its extension to the pure YM fields in the temporal gauge 
is presented below. 

The basic idea is that the Schrodinger wave functional 
 which represents the probability amplitude of 
simultaneously observing the field configuration  
 at the moment of time  can be seen as a joint probability
amplitude of 
simultaneously observing the respective values   at the  
spatial points  (at the moment of time ). 
Those amplitudes are 
given by the wave function  restricted to the 
Cauchy surface : . 
Using the result of,  in the temporal gauge 
 
the corresponding composed amplitude is written as 
([A^a_i()],t) = 
tr (1+) e^d_(A_i^a(),,t) 
 =: tr  ,  

where  denotes the restriction of the 
Clifford-valued wave function  to the Cauchy surface .
This Ansatz establishes a link between 
 
the Clifford-valued wave function appearing in precanonical  quantization 
and the Schrodinger wave functional resulting from canonical quantization. 








